dia business council usibc representing more than three hundred of the largest international companies investing in india he is also a member of board of directors of the dow chemical company member of the council on foreign relations and member of international business council of the world economic forum the government of india awarded him the civilian honour of the padma shri in  contents  early life  education  career  see also  references  external links early lifeedit born into a sikh family in khadki pune maharashtra in india where his father an army officer was posted the familys origin is from jalandhar in punjab his father is retired lieutenantgeneral harbhajan singh banga who is a decorated army general of indian army he is also the younger brother of another wellknown ceo m s banga banga grew up and schooled across india successively in secunderabad jalandhar delhi hyderabad and in shimla where he finished his schooling educationedit banga went on to graduate with a bachelor of arts honours degree in economics from st stephens college delhi university and mba from the indian institute of management ahmedabad  careeredit beginning his business career with nestlé in  banga spent the next  years working in jobs spanning sales marketing and general management he later joined pepsico and was involved in the launch of its international fast food franchises in india as the economy liberalized banga was vice chairman of the board of trustees of the new york hall of science and a board member of the national urban league he was formerly a business sponsor of citis african heritage network – nyc banga has a keen interest in social development issues and over the period from  to mid he spearheaded citis strategy in the microfinance sector across the world banga is a regular speaker at various fintech conferences and various leadership conferences he also appeared on the mad money show hosted by jim cramer on thursday  nov  banga was the keynote speaker at the nyu stern  graduate convocation on may   where he spoke about the importance of diversity in driving innovation and leadership he also was a keynote speaker for his alma mater the indian institute of management ahmedabad during the class of s convocation see alsoedit indians in the new york city metropolitan region referencesedit  a b reshmanth april   these ceos of indian origin will make you feel proud south report retrieved may     httpwwwmastercardcomuscompanyennewsroomceotransitionannouncementhtml  httpwwwmastercardcomuscompanyennewsroomceotransitionannouncementhtml  httpwwwwhitehousegovthepressofficepresidentobamaannouncesmorekeyadministrationposts  httpwwwlatestgktodaycomajaypalsinghbangaappointedasmemberofusadvisorycommitteefortradepolicyandnegotiations  padma awards  press information bureau government of india  retrieved february     httptimesofindiaindiatimescombizinternationalbusinessdelhiwhizajaybangabecomesmastercardceoarticleshowcms  temporary primary source  httpexpressbuzzcomtopiciimalumnusajaybangaisnewceoofmastercardhtml  httpwwwmastercardcomuscompanyennewsroomceotransitionannouncementhtml  httpwwwcnbccomid  httpwwwsternnyueduexperiencesternnewseventsbangakeynoteconvocation  httpsqzcomajaybangassixlessonsonleadershipastoldtotheiimaclassof external linksedit appearances on cspan retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleajaypalsinghbangaoldid categories american chief executives of financial services companiesbusinesspeople from puneliving peopleindian institute of management ahmedabad alumniamerican people of indian punjabi descentamerican sikhsindian emigrants to the united statesamerican chief operating officersrecipients of the padma shri in trade and industry birthshidden categories articles with hcards navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikip